title: Spaghetti Bolognese
summary: A classic Italian pasta dish with a rich and hearty meat sauce
instructions: Cook the spaghetti. In a separate pan, saute onions and garlic, then add the minced meat.Add tomatoes and simmer for 20 minutes.Combine with the spaghetti and serve

title: Chicken Caesar Salad
summary: A light and refreshing salad with grilled chicken, romaine lettuce and caesar dressing
instructions: Chop the lettuce and toss with Caesar dressing.Add grilled chicken croutons and Parmesan Cheese.Serve chilled

title: Vegeterian Tacos
summary: Delicious tacos filled with seasoned black beans avocado, and fresh salsa. A healthy and tasty option
ingredients: 1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed
1/4 crumbled feta cheese or vegan cheese(optional)
instructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add diced red onion , bell pepper and corn. Cook for 5-7 minutes until softened. Add cumin, smoked paprika, chilli powder, salt and pepper. Stir in black beans and cook for 3-4 minutes.Warm tortillas and assemble tacos with vegetable mixture, avocado and crumbled feta. Garnish with cliantro and serve with lime wedges

title: Pancake with Maple Syrup
summary: Fluffy Pancakes served with butter and drizzled with rich maple syrup .A perfect breakfast treat
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. In another bowl, whisk together milk, egg, melted butter and vanilla. Pour wet ingredients into dry ingredients and stir until combined.Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat, grease lightly with butter and pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.Cook until bubbles form, then flip and cook until golden brown.Serve with maple syrup
